    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-01T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-01T22:00:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48/4–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-02T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 2, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 3—12:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>556. Chinese Minister of Food<note n="9" xml:id="d47fn9">Hsu Kan.</note> issued
                    statement on March 27 that famine in northern Szechwan (Department’s 505, March
                    27) is not as serious as reported in press. However, in an editorial in March 31
                    issue of Communist <hi rend="italic">Hsin Hua Jih Pao</hi> it is claimed that
                    famine conditions extend to 26 districts in northwestern Szechwan, that the
                    Government has devised no practicable means of relieving conditions there and
                    that refugees from stricken areas are arriving in Chengtu in great numbers. Bulk
                    of editorial refuting above-mentioned statement of Minister of Food was
                    censored.</p>
                <p>Embassy is asking Attaché Service<note n="10" xml:id="d47fn10">Richard M.
                        Service, Vice Consul.</note> in Chengtu to investigate and report.<note
                        n="11" xml:id="d47fn11">Report not found in Department files.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
